   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# 02_limpieza - Limpieza y validación de ventas\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Objetivo: aplicar las reglas de calidad que especificaste: coerción de tipos, validaciones (nulos, rangos, dominios), deduplicación (último gana por _ingest_ts), trazabilidad (_source_file, _ingest_ts, _batch_id) y generación de outputs: `project/output/quality/ventas_quarantine.csv` y `project/output/clean_ventas.csv`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Notas importantes (leer antes de ejecutar):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Este notebook usa rutas relativas al repo (no uses rutas absolutas ni autodetección).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Si ejecutas el notebook desde un cwd distinto, cambia el cwd en una celda: `import os; os.chdir('RUTA_RAIZ_REPO')`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Explico las variables y pasos en los comentarios y en las celdas Markdown para que cualquiera pueda entenderlo.\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 1) Configuración y dependencias\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Librerías: pandas, pathlib, datetime, re, decimal.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Rutas: fijas y relativas a la raíz del repo.\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from pathlib import Path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from decimal import Decimal, ROUND_HALF_UP, getcontext\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import re\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import unicodedata as ud\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import uuid\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Rutas relativas (no auto-discovery)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"VENTAS_F = Path('project') / 'data' / 'drops' / 'ventas.csv'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PRODUCTOS_F = Path('project') / 'data' / 'productos.csv'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CLIENTES_F = Path('project') / 'data' / 'clientes.csv'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"OUT = Path('project') / 'output'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"(OUT / 'quality').mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"(OUT / 'parquet').mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Decimal para dinero (precisión suficiente)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"getcontext().prec = 28\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CENT = Decimal('0.01')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Patrones esperados\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PAT_P = re.compile(r'^P[0-9]+$')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PAT_C = re.compile(r'^C[0-9]+$')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Trazabilidad por ejecución\\n\",\n",
    "    \"_now_ts = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"_batch_id = 'nb-' + uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2) Lectura con trazabilidad\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `raw_df`: lectura literal desde CSV (todas las columnas como strings).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Añadimos `_source_file`, `_ingest_ts`, `_batch_id` y `_row_id` (orden de fichero).\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"if not VENTAS_F.exists():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raise FileNotFoundError(f'Ventas file not found at relative path: {VENTAS_F}. Ejecuta desde la raíz del repo.')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df = pd.read_csv(VENTAS_F, dtype=str)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Normalizar nombres (por si el CSV tiene 'fecha_venta' u otra variante)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df.columns = [c.strip() for c in raw_df.columns]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if 'fecha_venta' in raw_df.columns and 'fecha' not in raw_df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raw_df = raw_df.rename(columns={'fecha_venta':'fecha'})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if 'precio' in raw_df.columns and 'precio_unitario' not in raw_df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raw_df = raw_df.rename(columns={'precio':'precio_unitario'})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Trazabilidad mínima aplicada a todas las filas leídas\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df['_source_file'] = VENTAS_F.name\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df['_ingest_ts'] = _now_ts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df['_batch_id'] = _batch_id\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_df['_row_id'] = range(len(raw_df))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Leídas {len(raw_df)} filas desde {VENTAS_F.name} (batch={_batch_id})')\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### ¿Qué guarda cada variable? (explicación simple)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `raw_df`: DataFrame leído tal cual (columnas tipo string).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `df`: copia de `raw_df` donde aplicamos coerciones y normalizaciones.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `clean`: filas que pasan todas las reglas de validación.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `quarantine`: filas que fallan alguna regla; guardamos la causa para revisión.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `_ingest_ts`, `_source_file`, `_batch_id`: trazabilidad para saber cuándo y de dónde vinieron los datos.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `_row_id`: posición en el fichero (se usa para \"último gana\" en la deduplicación).\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3) Limpieza compacta (coerción + validación)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Reglas aplicadas (resumen):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `fecha`: ISO o timestamp UTC → date.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `unidades`: entero >= 0.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `precio_unitario`: decimal >= 0 (usamos Decimal para evitar floats en dinero).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Campos obligatorios: `fecha`, `id_cliente`, `id_producto`, `unidades`, `precio_unitario`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `id_producto` debe coincidir con `^P[0-9]+$` y `id_cliente` con `^C[0-9]+$`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Filas inválidas → `quarantine` con `quarantine_reason`.\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Helpers de normalización (texto y dinero)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def norm_text(x):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if pd.isna(x):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s = str(x).strip()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if s == '':\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s = ud.normalize('NFKD', s)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return ''.join(ch for ch in s if not ud.combining(ch)).upper()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def to_decimal_money(x):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if pd.isna(x) or x in (None, ''):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s = str(x).strip().replace(',', '.')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return Decimal(s).quantize(CENT, rounding=ROUND_HALF_UP)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Preparar df con columnas obligatorias\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = raw_df.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for c in ['fecha','id_cliente','id_producto','unidades','precio_unitario']:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if c not in df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        df[c] = None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Normalizar ids (trim, tildes removidas, mayúsculas)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for c in ['id_cliente','id_producto']:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df[c] = df[c].map(norm_text)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Coerciones\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['fecha'] = pd.to_datetime(df['fecha'], errors='coerce', utc=True).dt.date\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['unidades_num'] = pd.to_numeric(df['unidades'], errors='coerce')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['precio_unitario_dec'] = df['precio_unitario'].map(to_decimal_money)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Máscaras de validación\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mask_fecha = df['fecha'].notna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mask_unidades = df['unidades_num'].notna() & (df['unidades_num'] >= 0) & (df['unidades_num'] % 1 == 0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mask_precio = df['precio_unitario_dec'].notna() & (df['precio_unitario_dec'] >= Decimal('0'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mask_ids = df['id_cliente'].notna() & df['id_producto'].notna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mask_pat = df['id_producto'].astype(str).str.match(PAT_P, na=False) & df['id_cliente'].astype(str).str.match(PAT_C, na=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"valid = mask_fecha & mask_unidades & mask_precio & mask_ids & mask_pat\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Split clean / quarantine\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quarantine = df.loc[~valid].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"clean = df.loc[valid].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Añadir motivo en quarantine\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if not quarantine.empty:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def motivo_row(r):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        reasons = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if pd.isna(r['fecha']):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reasons.append('fecha inválida')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if pd.isna(r['unidades_num']):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reasons.append('unidades faltantes')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                if float(r['unidades_num']) < 0 or (float(r['unidades_num']) % 1 != 0):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                    reasons.append('unidades inválidas')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                reasons.append('unidades inválidas')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if r['precio_unitario_dec'] is None:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reasons.append('precio inválido')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if pd.isna(r['id_cliente']) or str(r['id_cliente']).strip()=='':\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reasons.append('id_cliente faltante')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if pd.isna(r['id_producto']) or str(r['id_producto']).strip()=='':\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reasons.append('id_producto faltante')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            if not PAT_P.match(str(r['id_producto'])):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                reasons.append('id_producto formato inesperado')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return '; '.join(reasons)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    quarantine['quarantine_reason'] = quarantine.apply(motivo_row, axis=1)\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 4) Dedupe y cálculo de `importe` (Decimal)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Clave natural: `(fecha, id_cliente, id_producto)`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Política: último gana por `_ingest_ts` y `_row_id` (orden de fichero).\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"if not clean.empty:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    clean = clean.sort_values(['_ingest_ts', '_row_id']).drop_duplicates(subset=['fecha','id_cliente','id_producto'], keep='last')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Calcular importe con Decimal para evitar floats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    importes = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for u, p in zip(clean['unidades_num'].tolist(), clean['precio_unitario_dec'].tolist()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if pd.isna(u) or p is None:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            importes.append(None)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            importes.append((Decimal(int(u)) * p).quantize(CENT, rounding=ROUND_HALF_UP))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    clean['importe'] = importes\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 5) Guardado de outputs y QA rápida\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Guardamos `ventas_quarantine.csv` y `clean_ventas.csv` en `project/output` y una versión parquet si pyarrow está disponible.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- QA rápida: porcentaje en quarantine y conteo por día.\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Guardados\\n\",\n",
    "    \"q_path = OUT / 'quality' / 'ventas_quarantine.csv'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quarantine.to_csv(q_path, index=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"clean_path = OUT / 'clean_ventas.csv'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"clean.to_csv(clean_path, index=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# parquet opcional\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if not clean.empty:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        clean.to_parquet(OUT / 'parquet' / 'clean_ventas.parquet', index=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        (OUT / 'parquet' / 'clean_ventas.csv').write_text(clean.to_csv(index=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Quarantine escrito -> {q_path} ({len(quarantine)})')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Clean escrito -> {clean_path} ({len(clean)})')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# QA rápida\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n_total = len(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n_quar = len(quarantine)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n_clean = len(clean)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pct_quar = (n_quar / n_total * 100) if n_total else 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Total filas: {n_total}, clean: {n_clean}, quarantine: {n_quar} ({pct_quar:.1f}%)')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if not clean.empty:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print('\\nConteo ventas por fecha (clean):')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(clean.groupby('fecha').size().rename('count').reset_index().to_string(index=False))\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 6) Resumen explicativo final (para la exposición)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Trazabilidad: guardamos `_source_file` (origen), `_ingest_ts` (cuando se ingesta), `_batch_id` (ejecución) y `_row_id` (posición en el fichero).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `quarantine` guarda filas inválidas con `quarantine_reason` para facilitar corrección origen.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `clean` contiene datos listos para modelado (dimensiones y fact tables).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Si quieres, convierto este notebook a `.py` o lo ejecuto como pipeline.\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
